sources.description:
Love, loyalty, and the hidden messages that bind them all.
In a covert mission against a spy ring, Philip's efforts are complicated when his brother Paul is framed. Through coded messages and unexpected alliances, the spies are thwarted, allowing for romantic resolutions amidst the intrigue.
 
Original title: Cipher Bureau (1938)
This film is subtitled in many languages.

Black & White version: https://youtu.be/_4uAApcxe6M


Director: Charles Lamont
Writers: Arthur Hoerl, Monroe Shaff 
Stars: Leon Ames, Charlotte Wynters, Joan Woodbury|, Don Dillaway
Genres: Colorized, Action, Adventure, Crime, Drama, Romance
